Hello everyone! English Speaking Club presents. Teens Talk! In each episode, we'll explore interesting topics, share helpful tips, and have fun chats to feel comfortable speaking English. So, grab a warm beverage, get cozy, and let's begin! Remember to follow us, guys! 
Fred: Hello, everyone! I'm your host, Fred, and I'm super excited, guys. You know this is our first episode. Today I have two guests, Rachel and Alex. Hi, guys! How are you both doing today?
Rachel: Great, Fred! Thanks for having us.
Alex: Same here. Excited to be here and chat with you guys.
Fred: So, today's topic is appearance and personality. Which one is more important for you? 
Rachel: Well, personality and appearance? To me, it's all about character. Easy-going, honest, and generous. These are all the things I really value.
Alex: I agree with Rachel. I think personality is the most important thing. But physical appearance also plays a role.
Fred: Really, Alex? What do you mean by that? Can you give us some examples?
Alex: Well… Beautiful, handsome, cute, slim, plump, and so on. But I think you can remember someone with their physical appearance.
Rachel: Yeah, you are right, Alex. But at the end of the day, the character really matters.
Fred: Good point, Rachel. OK, then, let’s have some fun. How well do you know each other? Let’s see! I’ll ask some questions, and you will answer. 
Alex: Questions?? 
Fred: Don’t worry, guys. They are easy. Here is the first one: Who is more generous?
Rachel: Hmm, more generous? Of course, Alex. He's more generous than me. Everybody knows this. You can always borrow something from Alex. Anything, pencils, erasers, books, cookies, and even money, haha.
Fred: Oo, Alex. You are a generous guy. Ok, who is more stubborn? You, or Rachel?
Alex: Haha, well, I hate to say it, but I'm pretty stubborn. Sometimes it's a good thing, but other times it gets me into trouble.
Rachel: Definitely, Alex is more stubborn than me.
Fred: (laughs): OK, another question. Who is more easy-going? 
Alex: I would say, Rachel. She is more easy-going than anyone else in our class. She stays calm and never worries. She's always up for trying new things and going with the flow. 
Fred: That's nice, Rachel. Who is more honest? 
Alex: Rachel.  
Rachel: Alex.
Fred, Rachel, Alex: haha
Alex: Rachel is definitely more honest. She always tells the truth, and she never tells a lie. 
Fred: Yeah, you can always count on her. 
Rachel: Thank you, guys! You’re so kind. But remember that everyone is unique and perfect.
Fred: You’re so right. Everybody is unique and special. 
Alex: Yes, yes, you’re right, guys. If you have a negative quality now, it doesn't mean you will always have it. People can change and grow. 
Fred: Thank you, Alex and Rachel, for sharing your opinions..
Rachel: Thanks again for having us. It was a lot of fun.
Alex: Yeah, I had a great time too.
Fred: Of course! It's always great to chat with friends and hear different perspectives.
So, that's it for today's episode of Teens Talk! Thank you to our guests, Rachel and Alex, for joining us and sharing their thoughts on appearance and personality. Remember, everyone is unique and special in their own way.  Thanks for listening, guys! See you in the next episode. Follow us and subscribe to our channel!
